        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-02-27 23:19:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(4 inline comments)\n\nThis isn't what I would expect for a NUMA scheduler (which I would think would make all cores on the same socket as partner ptlrpcd threads), but I'm open for suggestions.\n\nLiang is starting the work on a CPU partition that will balance thread-per-core with NUMA layouts, but until that work is done this seems like a good improvement for NUMA systems.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
