        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-03-07 01:53:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nSorry, my comment about the PDB_POLICY_NUMA not being used in this patch was due to confusion with PDL_POLICY_LOCAL (which is used by the RPC submitters).\n\nThe current PDB_POLICY_NEIGHBOR code was a simple mechanism intended as a placeholder that approximated a NUMA-aware policy until a proper NUMA-aware policy was added - see the comment at the beginning of ptlrpcd_bind().  The NUMA thread binding is being done in a separate project that is adding NUMA awareness to multiple levels of the Lustre stack (libcfs, LNet, ptlrpc, etc).  Since you have submitted a patch for this already, we should use it until the time that the CPU affinity APIs are added to libcfs.\n\nThe existing code for PDB_POLICY_NEIGHBOR can continue to be used if CONFIG_NUMA or HAVE_NODE_TO_CPUMASK is not available, since it still provides some cache affinity.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "d9fc6f1df29a8646406760d4c603a213a52b954b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 217,
        "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
        "email": "aurelien.degremont@cea.fr",
        "username": "adegremont",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-03-07 08:17:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nBy the way, you're talking about PDB_POLICY_NUMA but in the patch, it is still named PDB_POLICY_NODE.\nI think PDB_POLICY_NUMA is a well better name as \"node\" for an admin refers to a whole node (in a cluster), and not the internal NUMA nodes.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
