      "date": "2012-03-29 07:27:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nYou can determine indirectly that NUMA is supported by Lustre by looking if ll_ost_io threads are uniformly spread over the system NUMA nodes.\n\nThe cpu affinity of the ll_ost_io threads is conditionned by the same #define (CONFIG_NUMA and HAVE_NODE_TO_CPUMASK) than the NUMA implementation of the PDB_POLICY_NEIGHBOR binding policy.\n\nTo know if your system is NUMA, simply run 'numactl --hardware'.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
